	"title": "Ma famille — Family & possessives",
	"objective": "Name family members and say what belongs to you using possessives (A1: can describe family and immediate surroundings).",
	"bridge": {
		"title": "Bridge from Hindi / English: possessives agree with the THING, not the owner",
		"body": "In French, **mon** / **ma** match the gender of the noun owned, not the speaker: a girl still says **mon livre** (my book, masc.) and **ma sœur** (my sister, fem.). English “his/her” works the opposite way. Good news — Hindi already agrees like French: मेरा भाई (mera bhai, masc.) vs मेरी बहन (meri behen, fem.). Lean on that instinct. ⚠️ Note: **un parent** often means “a relative”, not only “a parent”."
	},
